    "Body": " Company Description EarthShare is an environmental philanthropy and impact organization that has distributed over $300 million in support of the nation\u2019s leading network of environmental and conservation organizations working to protect the health of the planet. For over 30 years, EarthShare has worked across industries and environmental issue areas to engage millions of individuals and workplaces as active participants in our mission. EarthShare participates in over 600 public and private sector workplace fundraising and engagement campaigns, delivers strategic environmental programing, and processes more than one million donor transactions and 4,000 grants to the nonprofit sector annually. With the power of a 500-member strong network of the most impactful environmental and conservation organizations behind us, EarthShare is inspiring and accelerating the environmental giving and action necessary to ensure a more sustainable and just future for all. Job Description Position Summary We are seeking a Regional Director for the Midwest region who will serve as an integral member of EarthShare\u2019s Campaigns & Membership team. The Regional Director, Midwest will bring passion for inspiring greater environmental action and giving; an understanding of the environmental landscape within the Midwest bioregion; and a proven track record of program development and management within the environmental sector. A newly created position, the Regional Director will report to the SVP, Campaigns & Membership, and work closely with the departmental team and other staff to steward, manage, and grow EarthShare\u2019s portfolio of workplace giving relationships, member and grantee relationships, and program initiatives in Illinois, Michigan, Ohio, and Wisconsin, and other areas within the region as assigned. The Regional Director, Midwest will also participate in the development and implementation of EarthShare\u2019s Midwest regional strategy to inspire and accelerate environmental giving and action, to include short and long-term goal planning; trend analysis in individual and workplace giving and engagement; nonprofit engagement and technical assistance; and advancement of issue specific bioregional priorities in collaboration with EarthShare\u2019s stakeholders and partners. Key Responsibilities Manage a portfolio of workplace giving campaign relationships, which currently includes a diversity of public and private sector accounts in Illinois, Ohio, Michigan, and Wisconsin, with other geographies in the Midwest as assigned; support existing campaigns while working to increase participation from current and new accounts. Manage one-on-one relationships with EarthShare\u2019s nonprofit members and stakeholders in the Midwest; provide support and feedback to members and stakeholders; cultivate and onboard new members. Work collaboratively with the Vice President, Impact to advance EarthShare\u2019s Impact Fund strategy; participate in cross-functional teams focused on innovation, thought leadership, and scaling up priority initiatives and promotion within campaigns. Serve as an effective advocate and public voice for the work, impact, and vision of EarthShare; represent EarthShare at campaign events, meetings, working groups; and establish the role as the public face of EarthShare in the Midwest. Work collaboratively with the Corporate Engagement team to support the implementation of corporate partnership programs and initiatives within the Midwest region, which may include participation in corporate advisory committee meetings and other program work. Work collaboratively with the Vice President, Operations to develop and analyze key performance and evaluative metrics for the organization\u2019s Midwest work. Work collaboratively with the Vice President, Communications & Marketing to communicate EarthShare\u2019s impact through its various programs and initiatives, and conduct and manage regular communications with Midwest members and stakeholders. Provide support for a variety of EarthShare initiatives, including management of EarthShare\u2019s presence on third-party giving websites; proposal development; fundraising; and other duties as assigned. Positively contribute to the organization\u2019s culture, accountability, transparency, and impact. Qualifications Demonstrated professional and personal passion for and alignment with EarthShare\u2019s mission and vision. Bachelor\u2019s degree required. 5-7 years of direct work experience in fundraising and donor/client relations with demonstrated success in customer service. Exceptional written, oral, and interpersonal communication skills. Self-motivated and ability to thrive in a dynamic, self-directed, and fast-paced environment. Collaborative working style with an ability to lead and build consensus. Strong knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite and Salesforce. Meticulous organization and record-keeping. Experience with member and donor engagement and workplace giving a plus. Public speaking experience and understanding of environmental subject matter preferred. Able to travel domestically when required. Additional Information Salary + Benefits This is a full-time position with the opportunity for location flexibility within the Midwest region, although close proximity to Chicago or Detroit is preferred. The starting salary is competitive, with the opportunity for periodic review and performance-based growth. EarthShare promotes a work-life balance and offers an excellent benefits package, including generous paid-time off; health, dental and vision insurance; and participation in a 403b retirement plan with a very competitive match. EarthShare is an equal opportunity employer; Veterans, people of color, people with disabilities, and LGBTQ candidates are strongly encouraged to apply. We are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, cultures, skills, and experiences, knowing that the more inclusive we are, the more successful we will be. To apply, submit your resume, a cover letter detailing relevant experience, and three references. Be prepared to provide contact information for references upon request. Please do not contact EarthShare\u2019s offices. The deadline to apply is July 20, 2020. To learn more about EarthShare, please visit our website at earthshare.org.Show moreShow less ",
